The Relativistic Energy-Momentum Relation

The total relativistic energy of an object can be expressed in terms of its relativistic momentum and its rest mass.

E^{2} = p^{2} c^{2} + m_{0}^{2} c^{4}

where:

E [var. scal. TotalRelativisticEnergy, M L^{2} T^{-2}, J] is the total relativistic energy of the object
p [var. scal. RelativisticMomentum, M L T^{-1}, kg m s^{-1}] is the relativistic momentum of the object
c [const. scal. SpeedOfLight, L T^{-1}, m s^{-1}] is the speed of light in free space
m_{0} [var. scal. RestMass, M, kg] is the rest mass of the object


